“So many will never understand how much sacrifice has been made to maintain the freedoms so many take for granted. May God Bless America and Bless be the families of our Fallen for they have paved the way. To our Fallen, you will never be forgotten because they are those of us who will refuse to kneel and continue the fight against the evil powers trying to destroy the best country on earth and our people. We will prevail! 

Today let it be a reminder that courage, honor, bravery is the corner stone of our nation best we can offer and our National cemetery’s are this undaunted sacrifice.

Remember them everyday for the day we will forget them, is they day our nation and our people have succumbed to complete tyranny.”

node.text: This happened to us today. These kids were welcoming us 🤍🥺🇺🇸 They wanted to thank Veterans.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by 𝐀𝐧𝐧𝐚 𝐏𝐚𝐮𝐥𝐢𝐧𝐚 𝐋𝐮𝐧𝐚 on August 31, 2021 tagging @forever21, @kyliejenner, @elleusa, @barstoolsports, @robsmithonline, @marines, @usarmy, @worldstar, @ourrescue, @usaf_recruiting, and @1stbn8thmarines. May be an image of text that says 'Please repost this. This week alone, the suicide crisis hotline for veterans has received over 35,000 calls. Our nation is hurting and our veterans are at risk of suicide. This image could save a life and we need to ensure our vets know they have support. If you are are a veteran, please know you are not alone & you did not serve in vain. Help is available and want every single member of our military to have these numbers: Veteran's Crisis Hotline: 1-800-273-8255 Or send a text, to: 838255 Share this, it could save a life.'.

node.text: 🙏🏼 We need you. 🙏🏼
